HEADWORD: Archilute
<hw>Arch"i*lute</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>archiluth</ets>,
It. <ets>arciliuto</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A large theorbo,
or double-necked lute, formerly in use, having the bass strings doubled
with an octave, and the higher strings with a unison.</def>⟦br⟧
